{"id":"pommels","term":"Pommels","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 4:12\">2 Chr. 4:12</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Chronicles 4:13\">13</a>), or bowls (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Kings 7:41\">1 Kings 7:41</a>), were balls or “rounded knobs” on the top of the chapiters (q.v.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["2 Chronicles 4:12","2 Chronicles 4:13","1 Kings 7:41"]}